                      (         lisp.asm):00809         ; puts_cased: X -> NUL-terminated string.  Like puts_native but routes
                      (         lisp.asm):00810         ; each byte through emit_a_cased so the printer's case-mode fold
                      (         lisp.asm):00811         ; applies.  Used for `T` / `NIL` / `#<CLOSURE>` / `#<MACRO>` /
                      (         lisp.asm):00812         ; `#<BUILTIN>` so they follow the user's chosen case.  Destroys X, A,
                      (         lisp.asm):00813         ; B.
